<p><strong>Abstract</strong>: In this talk I will discuss a range of academic research into agile methods. A huge amount has been written about agile methods, including assessment of specific techniques, their relationship with traditional methods, impact on project management, organisational culture and testing, how to integrate agility across the organisation, and so on. The talk will not be able to cover all of these aspects, but will focus on a range of areas related to general business disciplines. I aim to present some results of the research, but also to consider the approaches and theoretical stances adopted.&nbsp;</p>]]></description>
