                    <item>
              <title>Introduction to ELESIG</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/3356</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/3356</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<div>
<div>
<p>ELESIG is a community of  practice for researchers and practitioners interested in the learner experience of elearning.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<p>ELESIG is an international community of researchers and  practitioners in education and training who are involved in  investigations of learners' experiences and uses of technology in  learning. ELESIG members work together to share knowledge and practice  and develop a shared repertoire of resources which will be of benefit to  the community and the sector.</p>
<p>ELESIG is based in a <a href="/elesig.ning.com" target="_blank">Ning social network</a></p>
<p>Membership is free and while many members are from HE  and FE, we also welcome anyone interested in the learner experience of  learning technologies e.g., from HE, FE, schools, workplace and lifelong  learning, commercial training or any other sector.</p>
<p>ELESIG runs three face to face symposia per year and a number of  online events as well as discussions and opportunities to network  online. It is run by a Management Team of volunteers from various  educational institutions and a Community Manager.</p>
</div>
<p style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->ELESIG has created two spaces of interest to  its members on Cloudworks:</p>
<ul style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS-->
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS--><a href="/cloudscape/view/2062"><strong>ELESIG - Resources</strong></a>&nbsp;to  share and discuss resources produced by the ELESIG community</li>
<li style="cursor:auto"><!--NO CSS--><a style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 12px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #003399; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" href="/cloudscape/view/2047" target="_self"><strong>ELESIG  - Readings</strong></a>&nbsp;to share and discuss publications in the field  of learner experience research.</li>
</ul>]]></description>
          <pubDate>Mon, 12 Apr 2010 11:41:51 +0000</pubDate>
