<p>A guide to completing the skills audit and using the Mystuff e-portfolio for STM895. The workshop will discuss different types of evidence of skills development and how to submit evidence to the e-portfolio.</p>
<p><strong>James Bruce</strong> &nbsp;Deputy Associate Dean (Research &amp; Enterprise) for Science</p>
<p>James has teaching interests in the area of postgraduate study and he&nbsp; is chair of STM895 - Postgraduate research skills in science, technology, mathematics and computing and a member of the S825 Developing research skills in science course team. He currently teaches undergraduate courses in organic chemistry within the Science Faculty and is course team chair of the S346 Drug Design and Synthesis course team.</p>
<p>James&rsquo; research interests are broadly based around supramolecular photochemistry and the coordination chemistry of the lanthanide metals with applications in chemical sensing and medicinal chemistry. This research combines his interests in non-covalent interactions and photochemistry and the multidisciplinary aspect of the research is reflected in the projects, which range from those with biological applications to those with a more technological aim.</p>]]></description>
