<p>This session will focus on the structure and rhetorical moves of conference abstracts. As a group we will consider the criteria for effective abstracts, identify the key elements or &lsquo;moves&rsquo; in a number of abstracts from different disciplines, and look at some features of writing style that may show disciplinary variation. Some sample abstracts will be provided as a starting point for discussion, but you may also like to bring along an example&nbsp;from your own field, or perhaps an abstract you have written yourself.</p>
