              <description><![CDATA[<p>Research Skills required by PhD students D6: Recognise boundaries and draw upon/use sources of support as appropriate</p>
<h1>Check this skill</h1>
<p>By the time students complete a PhD, they should be able to answer &lsquo;Yes&rsquo; to most of these questions.</p>
<ul>
<li>Are you clear about your rights and responsibilities as a PhD student, and those of your supervisor(s)?</li>
<li>Do you understand the role of your mentor or Third Party Monitor? Do you know what they can help you with and what they can&rsquo;t?</li>
<li>Have you had your annual meeting with them? </li>
<li>Do you have any particular needs that shape or constrain your work (e.g., dyslexia, examination anxiety, cultural barriers to criticising, shyness)?</li>
<li>Can you describe how you are addressing those needs or compensating for them, in order to facilitate your progress? </li>
<li>Have you discussed your needs and strategies with your supervisors?</li>
<li>Can you describe how you might go about asking for help?</li>
<li>Can you identify sources of support available to you?</li>
</ul>
<h1>Evidence of this skill</h1>
