              <title>Involving students in the international research community</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/914</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/914</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>
From the University of Gloucestershire:
</p>
<p>
'From October 2006 to January 2007, 31 students took the Language &amp;
Ecology module, and were encouraged to take part in the international
research community through working with the Language &amp; Ecology
Research Forum - the main international forum for research in
ecolinguistics. The Forum links together a network of scholars, has an
online journal (Language &amp; Ecology ISSN 1745-3631), a range of
resources, and a dedicated section for the EZ102 Language &amp; Ecology
module was created. Right from the start it is suggested that students
think of themselves as contributors to the research community, actively
exploring the texts which surround them and sharing insights with the
community.'
</p>
